onboard floppy controller

     I suspect a bad onboard floppy disk controller in my board. Not only
     would
     Windows 95 not configure it(get yellow exclamation sign in front of
     device in
     System Devices, and configured thru dos
     compatiblity mode)but, the 1.44 drive
     will not format disks nor boot up from
     a Start Up disk. Files copied to it do
     not show up when I put the floppy disk
     in another computer.
     I sent the board to tech support, they sent
     it back(it could be a different board, I can't tell). Now, Windows
     95 shows the floppy controller and drive are configured properly,
     but, the drive acts the same. Naturally, I tried a different drive,
     double checked the ribbon cable connections (pin 1 to pin 1),
     even tried the board in another case/power supply.
     Can they fix an onboard floppy controller in a motherboard?
       [42]Reply With Quote Reply With Quote [43]Share on Google+
         ______________________________________________________________

