     I don't think so
     It would make no sense trying to repair onboard fdd-controllers.
     i would check if new BIOS fixes problems and would read the FAQ of
     the manufacturer.
     Another thing would be a bad cable. U might have connected it right
     (Pin 1 to Pin 1) but if there's a mistake on the cable it might be
     ur problem.
     Check out BIOS-settings and try to reinstall windows (if u haven't
     already done so..)
     Well just check these things out. If nothing helps, call the hotline
     of the MANUFACTURER.
     If the dealer really changed boards, it might be that there's are
     may boards out. check out the Hotline !! They might help u.
     Good Luck
     MxP
       [49]Reply With Quote Reply With Quote [50]Share on Google+
