     I've checked everything I could think of, before I sent it in the
     first time. While tech support had the board, I put in another I had
     laying around, it worked fine in the case, same ribbon cable, floppy
     drive, etc., it all worked fine.
     When they sent the/a board back, everything seemed to configure
     fine(System Devices), but, when I tried to use the floppy, got the
     same problems I had before, wouldnt load files from the floppy,
     wouldnt boot from the floppy, wouldnt format a disk. It would try,
     really straining , dragging, to do it.
     Gives all indications of a bad floppy drive controller. I never
     thought that there might be a fix in a bios. I will check into that.
     I doubt if I will be able to find the manufacturer. It's a cheap, no
     name board. Well, it's Soltek. (Not Soyo Tek)
     Laughing.
